The paper focuses on data mining and analysis of complex data sets, specifically sequential data, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The use of Formal Concept Analysis (FCA) and pattern structures is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the application of the method to healthcare data suggests a potential connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
